data.title: GSGS: In-Focus Phase Retrieval Using Non-Redundant Mask Data
data.name: gsgs
data.description: gsgs does phase retrieval on images given an estimate of the pupil phase, like one from a non-redundant mask

evidence: "What is available in this package: The core program here is gsalgo.py - this computes all the Fourier transforms, etc."
"I've written a short example driver, test_gs.py. You should be able to run it right from the command line: python test_gs.py"

The README describes domain-specific optics operations: "Set optical parameters - wavelength, pixel scale, telescope diameter, etc... Run gsgs using your PSF, known pupil, and pupil estimate" indicating it directly performs scientific/optical computations.
